        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 4:29PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 429 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Selmer, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Shiloh National Military Park, Forty Forks, Selmer, Good Hope, Bethel
Springs, Pebble Hill, Right, Hamburg, Adamsville, Crump, Phillips,
Tulu, Old Lawton, Hurley, Walkertown, Purdy, Cerro Gordo, Chambers,
Counce, and Hickory Flats.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM CDT for
west Tennessee.</instruction>
